  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The operating envelope is explicitly bounded (flow rate 1–7 L/min, rotational speed 2000–6000 RPM, inlet pressure 5–20 mmHg, hematocrit 35–45%, temperature 37±1°C) and validation sampling covers the declared domain with documented sparse-coverage caveats. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels. Decision: Accepted.",
