      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is the standard form for centrifugal pump hemolysis prediction. Model form uncertainty assessed via comparison of three alternative hemolysis model formulations (Arora, Zhang, Taskin) at the three validated operating points. NIH spread across formulations < 18%; the chosen model is centrally positioned within the spread. Model form uncertainty is included in the Monte Carlo UQ.",
